<h2>2. AIVA — Best AI Music Generator for Cinematic & Orchestral</h2>

<p><strong>Rating: 4.5/5 · <a href="/tool/aiva">Read full AIVA review →</a></strong></p>

<p><strong>Best for:</strong> Composers, game developers, and filmmakers needing orchestral or classical music</p>
<p><strong>Pricing:</strong> Free (3 downloads) · €15/mo (Pro) · €49/mo (Pro+)

<p>AIVA (Artificial Intelligence Virtual Artist) specializes in orchestral, cinematic, and classical compositions. It's the go-to tool for game developers, filmmakers, and content creators who need professional-sounding orchestral scores. AIVA was trained on over 30,000 classical music scores and can compose in styles ranging from Baroque to modern film scores.</p>

<p>AIVA gives you fine-grained control over composition — you can set the key, tempo, instrumentation, and emotional mood. The platform also supports MIDI export, making it easy to import AIVA compositions into DAWs like Ableton, Logic Pro, or FL Studio for further refinement.</p>

<p><strong>Key Features:</strong></p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Style selection:</strong> Orchestral, cinematic, jazz, pop, rock, electronic, world</li>
  <li><strong>MIDI export:</strong> Full MIDI files for DAW integration</li>
  <li><strong>Sheet music:</strong> Automatic score generation for live musicians</li>
  <li><strong>Custom datasets:</strong> Train AIVA on your own musical style (Pro+ plan)</li>
  <li><strong>Commercial license:</strong> All plans include commercial usage rights</li>
  <li><strong>API access:</strong> For developers integrating music generation into apps</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Pros:</strong> Best orchestral/cinematic quality, MIDI export, full creative control, commercial rights included</p>
<p><strong>Cons:</strong> Less suited for pop/electronic with vocals, steeper learning curve than text-to-music tools</p>

